"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:9.4.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">9.4.4</span> 標題：無酵餅（unleavened bread）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מַצָּה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： matsah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:3\">GEN 19:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:8\">EXO 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:15\">EXO 12:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:17\">EXO 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:18\">EXO 12:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:20\">EXO 12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:39\">EXO 12:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:6\">EXO 13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:7\">EXO 13:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:15\">EXO 23:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:15\">EXO 23:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:2\">EXO 29:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:2\">EXO 29:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:2\">EXO 29:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:23\">EXO 29:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:18\">EXO 34:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:18\">EXO 34:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:4\">LEV 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:4\">LEV 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:5\">LEV 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:9\">LEV 6:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:12\">LEV 7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:12\">LEV 7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:2\">LEV 8:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:26\">LEV 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:26\">LEV 8:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:12\">LEV 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:6\">LEV 23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:6\">LEV 23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:15\">NUM 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:15\">NUM 6:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:17\">NUM 6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:19\">NUM 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:19\">NUM 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:11\">NUM 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:17\">NUM 28:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:3\">DEU 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:8\">DEU 16:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:16\">DEU 16:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:11\">JOS 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:19\">JDG 6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:20\">JDG 6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:21\">JDG 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:21\">JDG 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:24\">1SA 28:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:9\">2KI 23:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:29\">1CH 23:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:13\">2CH 8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:13\">2CH 30:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:21\">2CH 30:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:17\">2CH 35:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:22\">EZR 6:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:10\">PRO 13:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:19\">PRO 17:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:4\">ISA 58:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:21\">EZK 45:21</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">希： ἄζυμος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： azumos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:17\">MAT 26:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:1\">MRK 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:12\">MRK 14:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:1\">LUK 22:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:7\">LUK 22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:3\">ACT 12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:6\">ACT 20:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7\">1CO 5:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:8\">1CO 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd1:11\">1ES 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd1:17\">1ES 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Esd7:14\">1ES 7:14</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0528_bread_unleavened.jpg\" alt=\"無酵麵包\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">無酵麵包 (© Edsel Little, CC BY-SA 2.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>無酵餅是一種又薄又脆的餅，在麵團發酵前快速烘烤而成。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>以色列人匆忙離開埃及，麵團還沒來得及發起來就烤成了餅。這種餅成為他們蒙救贖脫離埃及奴役的象徵，也是慶祝這救贖的逾越節的一個特色。有些獻祭也會用到無酵餅。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>「無酵餅」也可以翻譯為「沒有使用酵母做成的餅」或「沒有發起來的餅」。有些語言可能需要說：「沒有使用讓麺團發起來的東西做成的餅」。</p>\n<p>在<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:7\">1CO 5:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:8\">1CO 5:8</a> 這兩節比喻性的經文中，希臘文<em>azumos</em> 一詞指純潔真實的生命；除此之外，這個詞在新約中都是指除酵節。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
